            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hmm... I am not quite sure what can be the reason for this.\n\nJudging by the trace, the issue is that `vim.system({ 'git', 'init' }, { cwd = '...' }):wait()` exits before its `pid` is closed. The explicitly closed `pid` check is taken from [other test](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7bf2ab4b87e08807ca9fa1901ac915427428a928/test/functional/lua/system_spec.lua#L21-L22) and that exact `git init` call is done [in other place in this test file](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7bf2ab4b87e08807ca9fa1901ac915427428a928/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua#L1162) (although in `before_each` and not `it`).",
